                        <br/><br/><br/><h2>文 献</h2><br><ol><br><li id="R1"><span class='au'>Sato, M. & Sato, K.</span>: <span class="ti">Maternal inheritance of mitochondrial DNA by diverse mechanisms to eliminate paternal mitochondrial DNA.</span> <span class='so'>Biochim. Biophys. Acta, 1833, 1979-1984 (2013)[<a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/23524114" target="_blank">PubMed</a>]</span></li><br><li id="R2"><span class='au'>Sato, M. & Sato, K.</span>: <span class="ti">Degradation of paternal mitochondria by fertilization-triggered autophagy in <em>C</em>. <em>elegans</em> embryos.</span> <span class='so'>Science, 334, 1141-1144 (2011)[<a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/21998252" target="_blank">PubMed</a>]</span></li><br><li id="R3"><span class='au'>Al Rawi, S., Louvet-Vallee, S., Djeddi, A. et al.</span>: <span class="ti">Postfertilization autophagy of sperm organelles prevents paternal mitochondrial DNA transmission.</span> <span class='so'>Science, 334, 1144-1147 (2011)[<a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/22033522" target="_blank">PubMed</a>]</span></li><br><li id="R4"><span class='au'>Sato, K. & Sato, M.</span>: <span class="ti">Multiple ways to prevent transmission of paternal mitochondrial DNA for maternal iheritance in animals.</span> <span class='so'>J. Biochem., 162, 247-253 (2017)[<a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/28981751" target="_blank">PubMed</a>]</span></li><br><li id="R5"><span class='au'>Mizushima, N. & Komatsu, M.</span>: <span class="ti">Autophagy: renovation of cells and tissues.</span> <span class='so'>Cell, 147, 728-741 (2011)[<a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/22078875" target="_blank">PubMed</a>]</span></li><br><li id="R6"><span class='au'>Okamoto, K.</span>: <span class="ti">Organellophagy: eliminating cellular building blocks via selective autophagy.</span> <span class='so'>J. Cell Biol., 205, 435-445 (2014)[<a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24862571" target="_blank">PubMed</a>]</span